		<title>By: fry</title>
		<link>http://markos.gaivo.net/blog/?p=84&#038;cpage=1#comment-271</link>
		<dc:creator>fry</dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 05 Dec 2005 11:16:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://markos.gaivo.net/blog/?p=84#comment-271</guid>
		<description>i didn&#039;t have problems with padding on the side because all my buttons were very small. IE obviously creates a padding of ~25% of the text size and with small buttons that&#039;s ~5px.

the solution would be to add a width in ems for IE (width:16.5em; and width:10em; for the example) - the button resizes with the font almost perfectly. the background issue is solved by using background-color:transparent; (tested on win2k: moz175,ffx1,ffx15,opera8,ie5,ie55,ie6)</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>i didn&#8217;t have problems with padding on the side because all my buttons were very small. IE obviously creates a padding of ~25% of the text size and with small buttons that&#8217;s ~5px.</p>
<p>the solution would be to add a width in ems for IE (width:16.5em; and width:10em; for the example) &#8211; the button resizes with the font almost perfectly. the background issue is solved by using background-color:transparent; (tested on win2k: moz175,ffx1,ffx15,opera8,ie5,ie55,ie6)</p>
]]></content:encoded>
